    <item>
      <title>Metabolic activity from single‑cell and spatial transcriptomics with scCellFie</title>
      <link>https://earmingol.github.io/projects/software/sccellfie/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://earmingol.github.io/projects/software/sccellfie/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://pypi.org/project/sccellfie/&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://badge.fury.io/py/sccellfie.svg&#34; alt=&#34;PyPI&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://codecov.io/gh/earmingol/scCellFie&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://codecov.io/gh/earmingol/scCellFie/graph/badge.svg?token=22NENAKNKI&#34; alt=&#34;Codecov&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://pepy.tech/project/sccellfie&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://pepy.tech/badge/sccellfie/month&#34; alt=&#34;Downloads&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg&#34; alt=&#34;License: MIT&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;metabolic-activity-from-singlecell-and-spatial-transcriptomics-with-sccellfie&#34;&gt;Metabolic activity from single‑cell and spatial transcriptomics with &lt;strong&gt;scCellFie&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;scCellFie&lt;/strong&gt; is a Python‑based tool for analyzing metabolic activity at different resolutions, developed at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://ventolab.org/&#34;&gt;Vento Lab&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;It efficiently processes both single‑cell and spatial data to predict metabolic task activities.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;While its prediction strategy is inspired by &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/LewisLabUCSD/CellFie&#34;&gt;CellFie&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=&#34;https://lewislab.ucsd.edu/&#34;&gt;Lewis Lab&lt;/a&gt; (originally in MATLAB for bulk and small single‑cell datasets), &lt;strong&gt;scCellFie&lt;/strong&gt; adds multiple improvements such as marker selection, differential analysis, and cell‑cell communication inference.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
